After a spate of destructive fires, New York City is taking steps to snuff out sales of bootleg e-bike batteries. Mayor Eric Adams signed five bills that ban the sale of uncertified lithium-ion batteries. The city saw 44 fires linked to lithium-ion batteries in 2020, fire officials said. The number grew to 220 in 2022.
